Description: A rest on the flight into Egypt. Landscape with Joseph leading the ass to a river at centre left and two angels seated next to the Virgin at right, who is about to wrap the nude Christ Child in a shawl; copy in reverse after Herman van Swanevelt Etching
Curator's comments: This a copy in reverse, for the original etching by Swanevelt and comment see 1868,0822.758.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (8) (copy)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (monogram with the date 1791)
